15. **Use `tokio::io::duplex(8192)` for the McpServer.serve() pairing** — paired AsyncRead/AsyncWrite halves replace stdio for in-process testing. Pattern (from WO-0040 P2-W7 stdio handshake test):
    `let (mut client_to_server, server_in) = tokio::io::duplex(8192);
let (server_out, mut client_from_server) = tokio::io::duplex(8192);
let server_handle = tokio::spawn(async move { server.serve(server_in, server_out).await });
client_to_server.write_all(b"<JSON-RPC line>
").await?;
let mut response_line = Vec::new();
client_from_server.read_until(b'
', &mut response_line).await?;
let response: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_slice(&response_line)?;`.
    `serve()` returns when the input stream closes; tests close `client_to_server` (drop) before awaiting `server_handle`. Buffer size 8192 matches the tokio default.
